    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka inflation rises to 64.3-pct in August",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka\u2019s inflation in the 12- months to August 2022 accelerated to 64.3 percent in August from 60.8 percent in July, the state statistics office said.",
        "The widely watched Colombo Consumer Price Index grew 2.5 percent during the month to 235.8 points from 230.1 points.",
        "Sri Lanka\u2019s inflation galloped after two years of money printing and a collapse of the currency.",
        "The central bank has since allowed market rates to go to around 30 percent, reducing credit and outflows.  (Colombo/Aug31/2022)"
      ],
